## Part 4: Tenant Isolation & Authorization (1.5 hours)

### 4.1 Extracting Tenant ID from Context

```go
// In pkg/middleware/tenant.go

// GetTenantIDFromContext extracts tenant from JWT claims
func GetTenantIDFromContext(ctx context.Context) (string, error) {
    claims, ok := ctx.Value("claims").(*provider.Claims)
    if !ok {
        return "", errors.New("no claims in context")
    }

    if claims.TenantID == "" {
        return "", errors.New("no tenant in claims")
    }

    return claims.TenantID, nil
}
```

### 4.2 Tenant-Scoped Queries

**CRITICAL PATTERN:** Every database query must include tenant_id

```go
// CORRECT: Includes tenant_id in WHERE clause
func (dl *DataLayer) GetUser(ctx context.Context, id string) (*User, error) {
    tenantID, err := middleware.GetTenantIDFromContext(ctx)
    if err != nil {
        return nil, err
    }

    query := `
        SELECT id, name, email
        FROM users
        WHERE id = $1 AND tenant_id = $2  // CRITICAL: tenant_id check
    `

    var user User
    if err := dl.db.DB().QueryRowContext(ctx, query, id, tenantID).
        Scan(&user.ID, &user.Name, &user.Email); err != nil {
        return nil, err
    }

    return &user, nil
}

// WRONG: Missing tenant_id filter - exposes all users!
